Create the single serialization contract used by both new routes. Write apps/site/src/lib/get-llm-text.ts VERBATIM (TSDoc is present, Hard Rule 4):

import type { InferPageType } from 'fumadocs-core/source';
import { source } from '@/lib/source';
import { siteConfig } from '@/config/site';

/**
 * Serialize one docs page to clean markdown for AI consumption.
 *
 * Emits a stable header — the page title and its absolute canonical URL — then
 * the page's processed markdown body (frontmatter stripped, MDX compiled to
 * plain markdown). Used by the per-page raw route and by llms-full.txt so both
 * surfaces share one format.
 *
 * @param page - A docs page from the fumadocs source loader.
 */
export async function getLLMText(page: InferPageType<typeof source>): Promise<string> {
  const processed = await page.data.getText('processed');
  const url = `${siteConfig.url}${page.url}`;
  const header = page.data.description
    ? `# ${page.data.title}\nSource: ${url}\n\n${page.data.description}`
    : `# ${page.data.title}\nSource: ${url}`;
  return `${header}\n\n${processed}`;
}

LOCKED CONTRACT (do not deviate): Input is one loader page (InferPageType<typeof source>). Output, in order: an H1 "# {title}"; a "Source: {absoluteUrl}" line where absoluteUrl = siteConfig.url + page.url (e.g. https://dorkos.ai/docs/guides/foo); the frontmatter description as a paragraph ONLY if present; a blank line; then the processed markdown body. The URL is ABSOLUTE (matches llms.txt/route.ts:70 convention) — this is what makes "Open in Claude" honest (claude.ai is handed a fetchable canonical URL). Frontmatter is NOT serialized (getText('processed') already yields the body without frontmatter); title/description/Source are lifted into the header explicitly. Body headings are preserved verbatim.

Write the unit test apps/site/src/lib/__tests__/get-llm-text.test.ts (each case a purpose comment, no always-pass) using a FAKE page shaped { url, data: { title, description, getText } } — no real loader needed. Assert: (1) header order is H1 title, then "Source: " + absolute URL (siteConfig.url + page.url), then the processed body follows after a blank line; (2) the Source URL is absolute (starts with siteConfig.url and ends with the page.url); (3) when data.description is absent, the description paragraph is OMITTED (header is title + Source only); (4) when present, the description paragraph appears between the Source line and the body. Mock siteConfig.url if needed for a deterministic assertion.

FILES: apps/site/src/lib/get-llm-text.ts (new), apps/site/src/lib/__tests__/get-llm-text.test.ts (new).

ACCEPTANCE: get-llm-text.ts exports getLLMText with the exact contract above; the unit test proves header order, absolute URL, and the description-present/absent branches; typecheck + the test pass.

VERIFY: pnpm --filter @dorkos/site exec vitest run src/lib/__tests__/get-llm-text.test.ts && pnpm --filter @dorkos/site typecheck.

