Add a build-time full-corpus route that dumps every HAND-AUTHORED docs page as one markdown blob, joined through getLLMText. The 65 generated OpenAPI operation pages are filtered out (Decision D3). Mirrors the existing llms.txt static shape.

Create apps/site/src/app/llms-full.txt/route.ts VERBATIM (TSDoc present, Hard Rule 4):

import { getLLMText } from '@/lib/get-llm-text';
import { source } from '@/lib/source';

export const dynamic = 'force-static';

/**
 * Build-time full-corpus dump: every hand-authored docs page as one markdown
 * blob. Generated OpenAPI operation pages are filtered out (they carry an
 * _openapi marker and no prose); the API surface stays represented by
 * docs/api/openapi.json and the /docs/api links in llms.txt.
 */
export async function GET() {
  const pages = source.getPages().filter((page) => !isGeneratedApiPage(page));
  const parts = await Promise.all(pages.map(getLLMText));
  return new Response(parts.join('\n\n'), {
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain; charset=utf-8' },
  });
}

D3 FILTER — EXTRACT IT so it is unit-testable (the spec: "If the predicate is inlined, extract it so it is unit-testable"). Create apps/site/src/lib/is-generated-api-page.ts exporting a pure predicate isGeneratedApiPage(page): boolean (TSDoc). Primary rule: return true when the page carries the _openapi frontmatter marker (the deterministic signal every generated operation page sets — see docs/api/api/tasks/post.mdx:4, frontmatter key _openapi). Accessor: prefer page.data._openapi if the loader surfaces it on page.data. FALLBACK if the loader does NOT surface _openapi on page.data: the slug-prefix rule page.slugs[0] === 'api' && page.slugs.length > 1 (mirrors llms.txt/route.ts:55). EXECUTE picks the accessor the loader actually exposes; the filter INTENT is locked — drop exactly the 65 generated operation pages, keep every hand-authored page (including any hand-written docs/api overview at slugs.length === 1). The llms-full.txt route imports and negates this predicate; the same predicate is reused by task 1.6 (the D-A1 action-row gate) so A.4 and A.6 share ONE signal.

FORMAT (locked): each page rendered by getLLMText (H1 title + Source: URL + optional description + processed body), pages joined by a blank-line separator (two newlines). Served text/plain; charset=utf-8 (matches llms.txt/route.ts:198; the corpus is a text dump, not a single rendered document). Size ~56 hand-authored pages ≈ ~0.7 MB ≈ ~175k tokens — one static file per build.

Write apps/site/src/lib/__tests__/is-generated-api-page.test.ts (each case a purpose comment, no always-pass): a fake page carrying the _openapi marker → predicate true (excluded); a hand-authored prose page (no marker) → predicate false (kept); a docs/api overview page with slugs.length === 1 → false (kept). If EXECUTE selects the slug-prefix fallback accessor, test THAT branch instead so the test matches the shipped accessor.

FILES: apps/site/src/app/llms-full.txt/route.ts (new), apps/site/src/lib/is-generated-api-page.ts (new), apps/site/src/lib/__tests__/is-generated-api-page.test.ts (new).

ACCEPTANCE: GET /llms-full.txt returns text/plain joining the hand-authored corpus via getLLMText; the 65 generated API pages are excluded; the predicate is a standalone, unit-tested pure helper; typecheck + the test pass. The static-file/byte assertions land in the 1.6 build gate.

VERIFY: pnpm --filter @dorkos/site exec vitest run src/lib/__tests__/is-generated-api-page.test.ts && pnpm --filter @dorkos/site typecheck.

DEPENDENCIES: 1.2 (imports getLLMText). PARALLELIZABLE with 1.3 (disjoint route files, both only need 1.2). Spec cite: Detailed Design A.4 (verbatim route + D3 filter + fallback), Testing Strategy (Phase A unit — the filter predicate), Acceptance Criteria (Phase A, /llms-full.txt checkbox), Non-Goals (do not feed generated API pages into llms-full.txt).
